"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to Chronic Disease Management in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-27T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-27T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to Chronic Disease Management in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-27T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-27T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover effective methods for managing chronic illnesses in Turkey. Learn how you can improve your health and well-being with access to the right information and support!","name":"A Guide to Chronic Disease Management in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Chronic diseases are a significant health issue worldwide. In Turkey, the management of these illnesses is a crucial part of the healthcare system. In this article, we will cover the basics of chronic disease management in Turkey, including statistics, the most common diseases, government support, the healthcare system, and modern management methods.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-kronik-hastalik-yonetimi-temel-bilgiler-ve-istatistikler" class="wp-block-heading">Chronic Disease Management in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Chronic diseases are long-term health problems that often follow a progressive course. In Turkey, managing chronic illnesses is a key component of national health policy. According to data from the Turkish Statistical Institute (TÜİK), one in every three people in Turkey has at least one chronic disease. The most common of these illnesses include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Diabetes</strong></li>
<li><strong>Hypertension</strong></li>
<li><strong>Heart diseases</strong></li>
<li><strong>Asthma</strong></li>
<li><strong>Obesity</strong></li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Managing these conditions is critically important for improving individuals&#8217; quality of life and reducing the burden on the healthcare system.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-en-sik-gorulen-kronik-hastaliklar" class="wp-block-heading">The Most Common Chronic Diseases in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common chronic diseases in Turkey have a significant impact on public health. Here are the most prevalent chronic illnesses with brief descriptions:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Diabetes:</strong> Approximately 7 million people in Turkey have diabetes. Diabetes is characterized by uncontrolled high blood sugar levels and can lead to serious complications.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Hypertension:</strong> High blood pressure affects one in three people in Turkey. If left untreated, it increases the risk of heart attack and stroke.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Heart Diseases:</strong> Heart diseases are one of the leading causes of death in Turkey. Unhealthy lifestyles and genetic factors contribute to the rise of these conditions.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Asthma:</strong> Three million people in Turkey suffer from asthma. Asthma causes shortness of breath due to inflammation of the airways.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5. <strong>Obesity:</strong> The obesity rate in Turkey is steadily increasing. Obesity is considered a trigger for many chronic diseases.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also check out our article on <a title="Psychological Counseling in Universities in Turkey" href="https://https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-universitelerde-psikolojik-danismanlik/">Psychological Counseling in Universities in Turkey</a>.</p>
<h2 id="kronik-hastalara-devlet-para-veriyor-mu" class="wp-block-heading">Does the Government Provide Financial Support to Patients with Chronic Illnesses?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the government offers various forms of support for patients with chronic illnesses. The Ministry of Health provides the following services to support the treatment process for individuals with chronic conditions:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Free Medication:</strong> Patients with chronic illnesses can receive certain medications covered by their health insurance for free.</li>
<li><strong>Regular Check-ups:</strong> Public hospitals provide regular health check-ups for chronic patients.</li>
<li><strong>Rehabilitation Services:</strong> Rehabilitation services are available as part of the treatment for chronic diseases, and patients have access to these services.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These support systems facilitate patients&#8217; treatment processes and improve their quality of life.</p>
<h2 id="kronik-hastaliklarin-tedavi-surecinde-turkiyenin-saglik-sistemi" class="wp-block-heading">Turkey’s Healthcare System in the Treatment of Chronic Diseases</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s healthcare system plays a significant role in managing chronic diseases. The Ministry of Health has developed various programs for the prevention and treatment of chronic illnesses. These programs include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Public Health Programs:</strong> These programs promote healthy lifestyles through public awareness campaigns.</li>
<li><strong>Training Programs:</strong> Training on chronic disease management is organized for doctors and healthcare professionals.</li>
<li><strong>Health Information Systems:</strong> Digital systems are used to track the health data of chronic patients.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These systems make patients&#8217; treatment processes more effective and enhance the quality of healthcare services.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-kronik-hastalik-yonetiminde-kullanilan-modern-yontemler" class="wp-block-heading">Modern Methods Used in Chronic Disease Management in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Modern technologies and methods are used in the management of chronic diseases. Here are some of the modern methods commonly used in Turkey:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Telehealth Services:</strong> Remote monitoring of patients facilitates access to healthcare services. This is a significant advantage, especially for patients living in rural areas.</li>
<li><strong>Mobile Applications:</strong> Specially developed mobile apps for chronic patients help them track their treatment processes.</li>
<li><strong>Data Analytics:</strong> By using data analytics in chronic disease management, better predictions can be made about patients&#8217; health conditions, and personalized treatment plans can be created.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These modern methods make patients&#8217; treatment processes more effective while also increasing the overall efficiency of the healthcare system.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What support is available for chronic diseases in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, support for patients with chronic illnesses includes free medication, regular health check-ups, and rehabilitation services.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What treatment options does the government offer for chronic diseases?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Public hospitals provide regular check-ups for patients with chronic illnesses, and necessary treatment processes are offered free of charge.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What modern methods are used for chronic diseases?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Modern methods like telehealth services, mobile applications, and data analytics are used in the management of chronic diseases.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the most common chronic diseases in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most common chronic diseases in Turkey include diabetes, hypertension, heart diseases, asthma, and obesity.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What healthcare systems play a role in the treatment of chronic diseases?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s healthcare system plays a significant role in the treatment of chronic diseases through public health programs, training programs, and health information systems.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-04-27T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:29Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-chronic-disease-management-in-turkey';
