Guide for Students","inLanguage":"fr-FR","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie/","name":"Guide des cours et certificats de premiers secours en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-16T07:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-16T07:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"fr-FR"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Guide des cours et certificats de premiers secours en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-16T07:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-16T07:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Santé et Sécurité","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Participez à des cours de premiers secours en Turquie et obtenez un certificat ! Inscrivez-vous dès maintenant pour approfondir vos connaissances en matière de santé.","name":"Guide des cours et certificats de premiers secours en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les cours de premiers secours en Turquie occupent une place importante dans le domaine de la santé et de la sécurité. Ces cours aident les individus à apprendre comment agir en cas d&#8217;urgence, tout en offrant des avantages considérables dans la vie professionnelle. Dans cet article, nous aborderons l&#8217;importance des cours de premiers secours en Turquie, les avantages d&#8217;une formation certifiée, leur impact sur votre carrière, le contenu des formations, les points à considérer lors du choix d&#8217;un cours et la validité des certificats.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-ilk-yardim-kurslari-neden-katilmalisiniz" class="wp-block-heading">Cours de premiers secours en Turquie : Pourquoi y participer ?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Il existe de nombreuses raisons de participer à des cours de premiers secours. Tout d&#8217;abord, ces cours permettent d&#8217;acquérir des compétences qui peuvent sauver des vies en situation d&#8217;urgence. Une intervention correcte lors d&#8217;un accident peut augmenter les chances de survie de la personne blessée. De plus, ces formations renforcent la confiance en soi et permettent d&#8217;agir sans paniquer en cas d&#8217;urgence.</p>
<p>Par exemple, lors d&#8217;un accident de la route, une personne ayant des connaissances en premiers secours peut stabiliser l&#8217;état des blessés et effectuer des interventions vitales jusqu&#8217;à l&#8217;arrivée des équipes médicales professionnelles. De telles situations démontrent à quel point la formation aux premiers secours est cruciale.</p>
<h3>Où pouvez-vous suivre ces cours ?</h3>
<p>Il existe des centres de formation aux premiers secours agréés par le Ministère de la Santé dans les 81 provinces de Turquie. Les options les plus courantes et les plus fiables sont les suivantes :</p>
<ol start="1">
<li><b>Centres de formation privés agréés par le Ministère de la Santé :</b> C&#8217;est l&#8217;option la plus répandue. Vous pouvez trouver les centres de votre province en recherchant &#8220;Sağlık Bakanlığı Onaylı İlk Yardım Kursu&#8221; sur les moteurs de recherche.</li>
<li><b>Le Croissant-Rouge Turc (Kızılay) :</b> De nombreuses branches du Kızılay disposent de centres de formation aux premiers secours.</li>
<li><b>Les centres de formation AKUT (Association de Recherche et de Sauvetage) :</b> Dans certaines provinces, AKUT dispose également de centres de formation agréés.</li>
</ol>
<p><b>Remarque importante :</b> Pour que votre certificat soit valide, vous devez vous assurer que l&#8217;établissement où vous suivez la formation est accrédité par la Direction Provinciale de la Santé (İl Sağlık Müdürlüğü).</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">À ce sujet, vous pouvez également consulter notre article sur les <a title="Numéros de contact et services d&#039;urgence en Turquie" href="https://roadtostudy.com//turkiye-acil-durum-irtibat-numaralari-hizmetler/">Numéros de contact et services d&#8217;urgence en Turquie</a>.</p>
<h2 id="sertifikali-ilk-yardim-egitimi-almanin-avantajlari" class="wp-block-heading">Les avantages d&#8217;une formation certifiée en premiers secours</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Suivre une formation certifiée en premiers secours présente de nombreux avantages. Cette formation joue un rôle important non seulement pour la sécurité personnelle, mais aussi pour votre carrière professionnelle.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Avantages</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Opportunités de carrière</strong> : Dans de nombreux secteurs, notamment la santé, l&#8217;éducation et la sécurité, posséder un certificat de premiers secours est devenu une exigence.</li>
<li><strong>Conscience de la sécurité</strong> : Les titulaires d&#8217;un certificat deviennent plus conscients de la manière de se protéger et de protéger les autres.</li>
<li><strong>Gestion des urgences</strong> : La formation aux premiers secours permet d&#8217;acquérir des compétences en gestion des situations d&#8217;urgence, ce qui est un atout majeur tant dans la vie personnelle que professionnelle.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-ilk-yardim-egitimi-icerik-ve-surecler" class="wp-block-heading">Formation aux premiers secours en Turquie : Contenu et processus</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En Turquie, la formation aux premiers secours est généralement dispensée par le Kızılay, le Ministère de la Santé et diverses organisations privées. Les formations se composent de deux parties principales : théorique et pratique.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Contenu de la formation</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Formation théorique</strong> :</li>
<li>L&#8217;importance des premiers secours</li>
<li>Les gestes à adopter en cas d&#8217;urgence</li>
<li>Les types de blessures et les interventions de premiers secours</li>
</ul>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Formation pratique</strong> :</li>
<li>Massage cardiaque et respiration artificielle</li>
<li>Techniques de transport d&#8217;un blessé</li>
<li>Contrôle des hémorragies et bandage</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le processus de formation dure généralement 16 heures et se conclut par la remise d&#8217;un certificat aux participants.</p>
<h2 id="ilk-yardim-kursu-secerken-dikkat-edilmesi-gerekenler" class="wp-block-heading">Points à considérer lors du choix d&#8217;un cours de premiers secours</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Il y a quelques points importants à prendre en compte lors du choix d&#8217;un cours de premiers secours :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Accréditation</strong> : Vérifiez si le cours est accrédité par des organismes officiels comme le Ministère de la Santé ou le Kızılay.</li>
<li><strong>Qualifications des formateurs</strong> : Il est important que les formateurs soient experts et expérimentés dans leur domaine.</li>
<li><strong>Contenu de la formation</strong> : Renseignez-vous pour savoir si le contenu du cours est complet et à jour.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-ilk-yardim-sertifikalari-gecerlilik-ve-kullanim-alanlari" class="wp-block-heading">Certificats de premiers secours en Turquie : Validité et domaines d&#8217;application</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les certificats de premiers secours obtenus en Turquie sont généralement valables 3 ans. À la fin de cette période, vous devez suivre une nouvelle formation pour renouveler votre certificat. Ces certificats sont valables dans de nombreux domaines et constituent un avantage important dans le monde du travail.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Domaines d&#8217;application</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Secteur de la santé</strong> : Essentiel pour ceux qui souhaitent travailler dans les hôpitaux, les cliniques et les services d&#8217;urgence.</li>
<li><strong>Établissements d&#8217;enseignement</strong> : Important pour ceux qui vont enseigner dans les écoles et les universités.</li>
<li><strong>Clubs de sport</strong> : Il est attendu des personnes travaillant dans le domaine du sport de posséder ce certificat pour assurer la sécurité des athlètes.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="ilk-yardim-sertifikasi-kariyerinizde-fark-yaratin" class="wp-block-heading">Certificat de premiers secours : Faites la différence dans votre carrière</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En Turquie, les cours de premiers secours occupent une place importante dans la vie personnelle et professionnelle des individus. Ces formations, qui permettent d&#8217;acquérir des compétences pour sauver des vies en cas d&#8217;urgence, augmentent également les opportunités de carrière. Obtenir une certification en premiers secours est une étape cruciale pour assurer sa propre sécurité et obtenir un avantage concurrentiel dans le monde du travail. En complétant correctly la formation, vous pouvez devenir plus conscient de la manière de vous protéger et de protéger votre entourage.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Foire aux questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Qui peut participer aux cours de premiers secours en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les personnes de tous âges peuvent participer aux cours de premiers secours. En général, les participants de 18 ans et plus sont préférés.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Combien de temps faut-il pour obtenir un certificat de premiers secours ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Pour obtenir un certificat de premiers secours, une formation de 16 heures est généralement requise.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Comment puis-je renouveler mon certificat ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Vous pouvez renouveler votre certificat en suivant une nouvelle formation avant sa date d&#8217;expiration.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Combien coûtent les cours de premiers secours ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les frais de cours varient en fonction de l&#8217;organisme de formation et du contenu. En général, le coût se situe entre 500 et 1500 TL.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quel est le plus grand avantage de suivre une formation aux premiers secours ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le plus grand avantage de la formation aux premiers secours est d&#8217;acquérir la capacité de sauver des vies en intervenant correctement dans les situations d&#8217;urgence. Cela revêt une grande importance tant sur le plan personnel que social.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ce guide vise à fournir des informations complètes sur les cours et certificats de premiers secours en Turquie. Si vous envisagez de suivre une formation, nous espérons que ces informations vous seront utiles dans votre processus de décision. N&#8217;oubliez pas que chaque nouvelle expérience vous enrichit !</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-16T04:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-14T15:45:09Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'guide-des-cours-et-certificats-de-premiers-secours-en-turquie' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","canonicalPath":"/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/peraturan-lalu-lintas-dan-keselamatan-pejalan-kaki-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/regles-de-circulation-et-securite-des-pietons-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/","name":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","name":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p>As an international student planning to study in Turkey, below is the most essential information on <strong>Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety</strong> to help you in your daily life. In recent years, Turkey has made significant legal changes to improve pedestrian safety. Knowing these rules is crucial for both your safety and the safety of those around you.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Basic Rule of Pedestrian Safety: Pedestrians Have Priority</h2>
<p>The most significant traffic change in Turkey is the <strong>pedestrian priority</strong> rule.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Absolute Priority:</strong> When approaching a crosswalk that is <strong>marked with lines</strong> but does not have a traffic officer or traffic light, all drivers <strong>must stop</strong> and <strong>give the right-of-way</strong> to pedestrians who are crossing or about to cross.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> This rule has been made a legal requirement by Article 74 of the Highway Traffic Law No. 2918.</li>
</ul>
<p>For example, when you are waiting at a crosswalk, you can step onto the road to cross. Drivers are expected to yield and stop for you. However, the safest approach is to always <strong>ensure a vehicle is stopping</strong> before you step onto the road.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Basic Rules and Responsibilities for Pedestrians</h2>
<p>As an international student planning to study in Turkey, below is the most essential information on <strong>Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety</strong> to help you in your daily life. In recent years, Turkey has made significant legal changes to improve pedestrian safety. Knowing these rules is crucial for both your safety and the safety of those around you.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Basic Rule of Pedestrian Safety: Pedestrians Have Priority</h2>
<p>The most significant traffic change in Turkey is the <strong>pedestrian priority</strong> rule.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Absolute Priority:</strong> When approaching a crosswalk that is <strong>marked with lines</strong> but does not have a traffic officer or traffic light, all drivers <strong>must stop</strong> and <strong>give the right-of-way</strong> to pedestrians who are crossing or about to cross.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> This rule has been made a legal requirement by Article 74 of the Highway Traffic Law No. 2918.</li>
<li><strong>In Practice:</strong> When you are waiting at a crosswalk, you can step onto the road to cross. Drivers are expected to yield and stop for you. However, the safest approach is to always <strong>ensure a vehicle is stopping</strong> before you step onto the road.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Basic Rules and Responsibilities for Pedestrians</h2>
<p>Even though you have priority in traffic, as a pedestrian, there are also rules you must follow:</p>
<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Situation</td>
<td>Rule and Obligation</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Walking Area</strong></td>
<td>Outside of the roadway (car road), it is mandatory to use <strong>pedestrian paths</strong> (sidewalks) and <strong>shoulders</strong> (roadsides where there are no sidewalks).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Crossing the Street</strong></td>
<td>When crossing the street, you must use <strong>pedestrian and school crossings</strong> or <strong>intersection entrances/exits</strong>. It is forbidden to cross outside these areas (for example, from the middle of a main road).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Signalized Crossings</strong></td>
<td>At locations with pedestrian signals, you must obey the <strong>pedestrian lights</strong>. Entering the road on a red light is dangerous and risks a fine.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Traffic Flow</strong></td>
<td>Even on pedestrian paths, it is forbidden to act in a way that endangers or obstructs traffic.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Important Traffic Rules for Those Planning to Drive</h2>
<p>If you are considering driving in Turkey, you should pay special attention to these basic rules:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Speed Limits</h3>
<p>Speed limits vary in residential areas, intercity roads, and motorways. In general:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Within Residential Areas:</strong> Generally 50 km/h.</li>
<li><strong>Intercity Roads:</strong> 90 km/h.</li>
<li><strong>Motorways:</strong> Generally 130 or 140 km/h.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Driving Violations</h3>
<p>The most common violations that lead to high fines are:</p>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Driving Under the Influence (DUI):</strong> It is strictly forbidden and has very severe penalties (ranging from fines and license suspension to imprisonment).</li>
<li><strong>Seat Belts:</strong> It is <strong>mandatory for the driver and passengers to wear them.</strong></li>
<li><strong>Mobile Phones:</strong> Talking or texting on a mobile phone while driving (including when stopped in traffic) is prohibited.</li>
<li><strong>Running a Red Light:</strong> Running a red light carries a high fine and poses a major risk to life.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Penalties</h3>
<p>Those who violate traffic rules are subject to an <strong>Administrative Fine</strong>. If you pay <a href="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">within <strong>15 days</strong> of receiving the fine notification</a>, you can usually benefit from a <strong>25% discount</strong>.</p>
<p>It is important to research topics such as the validity period of your international or foreign driver&#8217;s license for use in Turkey and the requirement to convert it to a Turkish license after that period.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the traffic rules in Turkey?</h3>
<p>Traffic rules in Turkey are regulated by the <strong>Highway Traffic Law No. 2918</strong>. The basic rules are to obey speed limits, wear a seat belt, not use a mobile phone while driving, not drive under the influence, and respect <strong>pedestrian priority</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the traffic rules for pedestrians?</h3>
<p>Pedestrians must use <strong>sidewalks and pedestrian paths</strong> and should prefer <strong>pedestrian and school crossings</strong> when crossing the street. It is mandatory to obey pedestrian signals at signalized crossings. At designated crossings, they <strong>have priority over vehicles</strong> (HTL Article 74).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are 10 traffic rules?</h3>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Wear a <strong>seat belt</strong>.</li>
<li>Obey speed limits.</li>
<li>Do not drive <strong>under the influence</strong>.</li>
<li>Stop at <strong>red lights</strong>.</li>
<li>Maintain a safe following distance.</li>
<li><strong>Yield to pedestrians.</strong></li>
<li>Use turn signals when turning.</li>
<li>Do not use a <strong>phone</strong> while driving.</li>
<li>Avoid improper overtaking.</li>
<li>Obey traffic signs.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What should we do to ensure safety in traffic?</h3>
<p>To ensure safety in traffic, we should always practice <strong>defensive driving</strong> techniques and avoid driving when tired or sleepy. Strictly following the rules, especially <strong>slowing down at pedestrian and school crossings</strong>, and being <strong>respectful</strong> to other drivers is essential.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-04-21T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:17Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","canonicalPath":"/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/peraturan-lalu-lintas-dan-keselamatan-pejalan-kaki-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/regles-de-circulation-et-securite-des-pietons-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/","name":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-21T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Planning to study in Turkey? As an international student, understanding local traffic rules is crucial for your safety. This guide covers the key regulations for pedestrians and drivers to help you navigate your new home safely.","name":"Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p>As an international student planning to study in Turkey, below is the most essential information on <strong>Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety</strong> to help you in your daily life. In recent years, Turkey has made significant legal changes to improve pedestrian safety. Knowing these rules is crucial for both your safety and the safety of those around you.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Basic Rule of Pedestrian Safety: Pedestrians Have Priority</h2>
<p>The most significant traffic change in Turkey is the <strong>pedestrian priority</strong> rule.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Absolute Priority:</strong> When approaching a crosswalk that is <strong>marked with lines</strong> but does not have a traffic officer or traffic light, all drivers <strong>must stop</strong> and <strong>give the right-of-way</strong> to pedestrians who are crossing or about to cross.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> This rule has been made a legal requirement by Article 74 of the Highway Traffic Law No. 2918.</li>
</ul>
<p>For example, when you are waiting at a crosswalk, you can step onto the road to cross. Drivers are expected to yield and stop for you. However, the safest approach is to always <strong>ensure a vehicle is stopping</strong> before you step onto the road.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Basic Rules and Responsibilities for Pedestrians</h2>
<p>As an international student planning to study in Turkey, below is the most essential information on <strong>Traffic Rules and Pedestrian Safety</strong> to help you in your daily life. In recent years, Turkey has made significant legal changes to improve pedestrian safety. Knowing these rules is crucial for both your safety and the safety of those around you.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Basic Rule of Pedestrian Safety: Pedestrians Have Priority</h2>
<p>The most significant traffic change in Turkey is the <strong>pedestrian priority</strong> rule.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Absolute Priority:</strong> When approaching a crosswalk that is <strong>marked with lines</strong> but does not have a traffic officer or traffic light, all drivers <strong>must stop</strong> and <strong>give the right-of-way</strong> to pedestrians who are crossing or about to cross.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> This rule has been made a legal requirement by Article 74 of the Highway Traffic Law No. 2918.</li>
<li><strong>In Practice:</strong> When you are waiting at a crosswalk, you can step onto the road to cross. Drivers are expected to yield and stop for you. However, the safest approach is to always <strong>ensure a vehicle is stopping</strong> before you step onto the road.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Basic Rules and Responsibilities for Pedestrians</h2>
<p>Even though you have priority in traffic, as a pedestrian, there are also rules you must follow:</p>
<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Situation</td>
<td>Rule and Obligation</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Walking Area</strong></td>
<td>Outside of the roadway (car road), it is mandatory to use <strong>pedestrian paths</strong> (sidewalks) and <strong>shoulders</strong> (roadsides where there are no sidewalks).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Crossing the Street</strong></td>
<td>When crossing the street, you must use <strong>pedestrian and school crossings</strong> or <strong>intersection entrances/exits</strong>. It is forbidden to cross outside these areas (for example, from the middle of a main road).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Signalized Crossings</strong></td>
<td>At locations with pedestrian signals, you must obey the <strong>pedestrian lights</strong>. Entering the road on a red light is dangerous and risks a fine.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Traffic Flow</strong></td>
<td>Even on pedestrian paths, it is forbidden to act in a way that endangers or obstructs traffic.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Important Traffic Rules for Those Planning to Drive</h2>
<p>If you are considering driving in Turkey, you should pay special attention to these basic rules:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Speed Limits</h3>
<p>Speed limits vary in residential areas, intercity roads, and motorways. In general:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Within Residential Areas:</strong> Generally 50 km/h.</li>
<li><strong>Intercity Roads:</strong> 90 km/h.</li>
<li><strong>Motorways:</strong> Generally 130 or 140 km/h.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Driving Violations</h3>
<p>The most common violations that lead to high fines are:</p>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Driving Under the Influence (DUI):</strong> It is strictly forbidden and has very severe penalties (ranging from fines and license suspension to imprisonment).</li>
<li><strong>Seat Belts:</strong> It is <strong>mandatory for the driver and passengers to wear them.</strong></li>
<li><strong>Mobile Phones:</strong> Talking or texting on a mobile phone while driving (including when stopped in traffic) is prohibited.</li>
<li><strong>Running a Red Light:</strong> Running a red light carries a high fine and poses a major risk to life.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Penalties</h3>
<p>Those who violate traffic rules are subject to an <strong>Administrative Fine</strong>. If you pay <a href="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">within <strong>15 days</strong> of receiving the fine notification</a>, you can usually benefit from a <strong>25% discount</strong>.</p>
<p>It is important to research topics such as the validity period of your international or foreign driver&#8217;s license for use in Turkey and the requirement to convert it to a Turkish license after that period.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the traffic rules in Turkey?</h3>
<p>Traffic rules in Turkey are regulated by the <strong>Highway Traffic Law No. 2918</strong>. The basic rules are to obey speed limits, wear a seat belt, not use a mobile phone while driving, not drive under the influence, and respect <strong>pedestrian priority</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the traffic rules for pedestrians?</h3>
<p>Pedestrians must use <strong>sidewalks and pedestrian paths</strong> and should prefer <strong>pedestrian and school crossings</strong> when crossing the street. It is mandatory to obey pedestrian signals at signalized crossings. At designated crossings, they <strong>have priority over vehicles</strong> (HTL Article 74).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are 10 traffic rules?</h3>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li>Wear a <strong>seat belt</strong>.</li>
<li>Obey speed limits.</li>
<li>Do not drive <strong>under the influence</strong>.</li>
<li>Stop at <strong>red lights</strong>.</li>
<li>Maintain a safe following distance.</li>
<li><strong>Yield to pedestrians.</strong></li>
<li>Use turn signals when turning.</li>
<li>Do not use a <strong>phone</strong> while driving.</li>
<li>Avoid improper overtaking.</li>
<li>Obey traffic signs.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What should we do to ensure safety in traffic?</h3>
<p>To ensure safety in traffic, we should always practice <strong>defensive driving</strong> techniques and avoid driving when tired or sleepy. Strictly following the rules, especially <strong>slowing down at pedestrian and school crossings</strong>, and being <strong>respectful</strong> to other drivers is essential.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-04-21T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:51:17Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Türkiye''de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","description":"Türkiye''de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Türkiye''de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Türkiye''de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Türkiye''de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Türkiye''de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği","canonicalPath":"/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/traffic-rules-and-pedestrian-safety-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/peraturan-lalu-lintas-dan-keselamatan-pejalan-kaki-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/regles-de-circulation-et-securite-des-pietons-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"tr","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-10-27T07:34:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:49:54+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"tr"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Türkiye&#039;de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","keywords":"Trafik Kuralları","datePublished":"2025-10-27T07:34:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:49:54+03:00","articleSection":"Sağlık ve Güvenlik","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Türkiye&#039;de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"tr","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel <strong>Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği</strong> bilgileri aşağıdadır. Türkiye, son yıllarda yaya güvenliğini artırmak için önemli yasal düzenlemeler yaptı. Bu kuralları bilmek hem sizin hem de çevrenizdekilerin güvenliği için çok önemlidir.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Yaya Güvenliğinde Temel Kural: Öncelik Yayanın</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;deki en önemli trafik değişikliği, <strong>yaya önceliği</strong> kuralıdır.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Mutlak Öncelik:</strong> Görevli bir trafik polisi veya ışıklı trafik işaretinin bulunmadığı, ancak <strong>çizgilerle belirlenmiş</strong> yaya geçitlerine yaklaşan tüm sürücüler <strong>durmak</strong> ve geçmek üzere olan yayalara <strong>ilk geçiş hakkını vermek zorundadır.</strong></li>



<li><strong>Kanun Maddesi:</strong> Bu kural, 2918 Sayılı Karayolları Trafik Kanunu&#8217;nun 74. maddesiyle yasal zorunluluk haline getirilmiştir.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Örneğin, bir yaya geçidinde durduğunuzda, karşıya geçmek için yola adım atabilirsiniz. Sürücülerin size yol vermesi ve durması beklenir. Ancak, her zaman <strong>bir aracın duracağından emin olarak</strong> yola çıkmanız en güvenli yaklaşımdır.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Yayalar İçin Temel Kurallar ve Sorumluluklar</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de eğitim almayı planlayan uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak, günlük yaşamınızda size yardımcı olacak en temel <strong>Trafik Kuralları ve Yaya Güvenliği</strong> bilgileri aşağıdadır. Türkiye, son yıllarda yaya güvenliğini artırmak için önemli yasal düzenlemeler yaptı. Bu kuralları bilmek hem sizin hem de çevrenizdekilerin güvenliği için çok önemlidir.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Yaya Güvenliğinde Temel Kural: Öncelik Yayanın</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;deki en önemli trafik değişikliği, <strong>yaya önceliği</strong> kuralıdır.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Mutlak Öncelik:</strong> Görevli bir trafik polisi veya ışıklı trafik işaretinin bulunmadığı, ancak <strong>çizgilerle belirlenmiş</strong> yaya geçitlerine yaklaşan tüm sürücüler <strong>durmak</strong> ve geçmek üzere olan yayalara <strong>ilk geçiş hakkını vermek zorundadır.</strong></li>



<li><strong>Kanun Maddesi:</strong> Bu kural, 2918 Sayılı Karayolları Trafik Kanunu&#8217;nun 74. maddesiyle yasal zorunluluk haline getirilmiştir.</li>



<li><strong>Pratikte Anlamı:</strong> Bir yaya geçidinde durduğunuzda, karşıya geçmek için yola adım atabilirsiniz. Sürücülerin size yol vermesi ve durması beklenir. Ancak, her zaman <strong>bir aracın duracağından emin olarak</strong> yola çıkmanız en güvenli yaklaşımdır.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Yayalar İçin Temel Kurallar ve Sorumluluklar</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Trafikte öncelik size ait olsa da, yaya olarak sizin de uymanız gereken kurallar vardır:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><td>Durum</td><td>Kural ve Yükümlülük</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Yürüme Alanı</strong></td><td>Taşıt yolu (araba yolu) dışında, <strong>yaya yolları</strong> (kaldırımlar) ve <strong>banketleri</strong> (yaya yolu olmayan yol kenarları) kullanmak zorunludur.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Karşıdan Karşıya Geçiş</strong></td><td>Karşıya geçerken mutlaka <strong>yaya ve okul geçitlerini</strong> veya <strong>kavşak giriş/çıkışlarını</strong> kullanın. Bu alanlar dışında (örneğin ana yol ortasından) geçmek yasaktır.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Işıklı Geçitler</strong></td><td>Yaya ışıkları olan yerlerde kesinlikle <strong>yaya ışıklarına</strong> uyun. Kırmızı ışıkta yola girmek tehlikelidir ve para cezası riski doğurur.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Trafik Akışı</strong></td><td>Yaya yollarında dahi trafiği tehlikeye düşürecek veya engelleyecek şekilde davranmak yasaktır.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Araç Kullanmayı Düşünenler İçin Önemli Trafik Kuralları</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer Türkiye&#8217;de araç kullanmayı düşünüyorsanız, şu temel kurallara özellikle dikkat etmelisiniz:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Hız Limitleri</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Hız limitleri yerleşim yerleri, şehirler arası yollar ve otoyollarda değişiklik gösterir. Genel olarak:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Yerleşim Yeri İçi:</strong> Genellikle 50 km/s.</li>



<li><strong>Şehirler Arası Yollar:</strong> 90 km/s.</li>



<li><strong>Otoyollar:</strong> Genellikle 130 veya 140 km/s.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Sürüş İhlalleri</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En sık rastlanan ve yüksek cezalara yol açan ihlaller şunlardır:</p>



<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Alkollü Araç Kullanımı:</strong> Kesinlikle yasaktır ve çok ağır cezaları vardır (para cezası, ehliyete el koyma ve hapis cezasına kadar gidebilir).</li>



<li><strong>Emniyet Kemeri:</strong> Sürücü ve yolcular için <strong>mutlaka takılması zorunludur.</strong></li>



<li><strong>Cep Telefonu:</strong> Seyir halindeyken (trafikte dururken dâhil) cep telefonuyla konuşmak veya mesajlaşmak yasaktır.</li>



<li><strong>Kırmızı Işık İhlali:</strong> Kırmızı ışıkta geçmek, hem yüksek para cezası hem de can güvenliği açısından büyük risk taşır.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Cezalar</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Trafik kurallarını ihlal edenlere <strong>İdari Para Cezası</strong> uygulanır. <a href="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.akademikhukuk.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cezayı tebliğ aldıktan sonra <strong>15 gün içinde</strong></a> ödeme yaparsanız, genellikle <strong>%25 oranında indirimden</strong> faydalanabilirsiniz.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de araç kullanmak için uluslararası ehliyetinizin ya da yabancı ehliyetinizin kullanım süresi ve bu süreden sonra Türk ehliyetine çevirme zorunluluğu gibi konuları araştırmanız önemlidir.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Sıkça Sorulan Sorular</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Türkiye&#8217;de trafik kuralları nelerdir?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de trafik kuralları <strong>2918 Sayılı Karayolları Trafik Kanunu</strong> ile düzenlenir. Temel kurallar hız limitlerine uymak, emniyet kemeri takmak, seyir halinde cep telefonu kullanmamak, alkollü araç kullanmamak ve <strong>yaya önceliğine</strong> riayet etmektir.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Yayalar için trafik kuralları nelerdir?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yayalar, <strong>kaldırımları ve yaya yollarını</strong> kullanmalı, karşıya geçerken <strong>yaya ve okul geçitlerini</strong> tercih etmelidir. Işıklı geçitlerde yaya sinyaline uymak zorunludur. Belirlenmiş geçitlerde <strong>araçlara karşı önceliğe sahiptirler</strong> (KTK Madde 74).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">10 tane trafik kuralları nelerdir?</h3>



<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Emniyet kemeri</strong> takmak.</li>



<li>Hız limitlerine uymak.</li>



<li><strong>Alkollü</strong> araç kullanmamak.</li>



<li><strong>Kırmızı ışıkta</strong> durmak.</li>



<li>Takip mesafesini korumak.</li>



<li><strong>Yayalara yol</strong> vermek.</li>



<li>Dönüşlerde sinyal vermek.</li>



<li>Seyir halinde <strong>telefon</strong> kullanmamak.</li>



<li>Hatalı sollama yapmamak.</li>



<li>Trafik işaretlerine uymak.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Trafikte güvenliği sağlamak için neler yapmalıyız?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Trafikte güvenliği sağlamak için daima <strong>defansif sürüş</strong> tekniklerini uygulamalı, yorgun ve uykusuz araç kullanmaktan kaçınmalıyız. Kurallara harfiyen uymak, özellikle <strong>yaya ve okul geçitlerinde yavaşlamak</strong> ve diğer sürücülere karşı <strong>saygılı olmak</strong> esastır.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-10-27T04:34:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:49:54Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiyede-trafik-kurallari-ve-yaya-guvenligi';
