":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey/","name":"Combating Addiction and Support Services in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-20T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-20T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Combating Addiction and Support Services in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-20T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-20T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about the resources and support services available for combating addiction in Turkey. Take action to get support now and take the first step toward a healthy life!","name":"Combating Addiction and Support Services in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 id="turkiyede-bagimlilik-sorunlari-gencler-uzerindeki-etkileri" class="wp-block-heading">Addiction Problems in Turkey: The Impact on Young People</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Addiction has become a widespread problem, especially among young people. Various types of addiction, such as alcohol, drug, and technology addiction, negatively affect the physical and mental health of youth. For example, according to one study, 30% of young people have used an illicit substance at least once. This situation has serious negative effects on school attendance, social relationships, and overall quality of life. To enhance young people&#8217;s ability to combat addiction, it is essential for families and educational institutions to provide support.</p>
<h2 id="bagimlilikla-mucadelede-turkiyedeki-destek-hizmetleri" class="wp-block-heading">Support Services for Combating Addiction in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a variety of support services in the field of combating addiction. The Ministry of Health has opened numerous centers for addiction treatment and rehabilitation. In these centers, psychological support, group therapy, and individual counseling services are provided to help individuals cope with addiction.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Support Services</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Helplines:</strong> There are 24-hour helplines in Turkey for individuals experiencing problems with addiction.</li>
<li><strong>Rehabilitation Centers:</strong> Specialized rehabilitation centers are available for alcohol and substance addiction treatment.</li>
<li><strong>Community Support Programs:</strong> Local governments and non-governmental organizations organize various community support programs for individuals combating addiction.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also read our article on <a title="Alcohol and Substance Use in Turkey: Legal Status" href="https://roadtostudy.com//turkiyede-alkol-madde-kullanimi-yasal-durumlar/">Alcohol and Substance Use in Turkey: Legal Status</a>.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-bagimlilik-ile-ilgili-yasal-duzenlemeler-ve-bilinmesi-gerekenler" class="wp-block-heading">Legal Regulations Concerning Addiction in Turkey and What You Need to Know</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the fight against addiction is also supported by legal regulations. The use and trafficking of illicit substances are considered serious crimes under the Turkish Penal Code. Additionally, there are various laws and regulations aimed at combating addiction.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Legal Regulations</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Law on the Prevention of Illicit Substance Use:</strong> This law was enacted to prevent the use of illicit substances and to regulate treatment services.</li>
<li><strong>Regulation on Addiction Treatment:</strong> This is a regulation that sets the necessary standards for addiction treatment.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How is addiction treated in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Addiction treatment is generally carried out through psychotherapy, group therapy, and, when necessary, medication. The treatment process is customized according to the individual&#8217;s needs.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What support services are available for combating addiction?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, there are various services such as rehabilitation centers, helplines, and community support programs.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the legal consequences of illicit substance use?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The use of illicit substances is a crime according to the Turkish Penal Code and has serious legal consequences. Users may be directed to treatment programs.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the role of families in combating addiction?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Families play a crucial role in the fight against addiction. It is the family&#8217;s responsibility to provide a supportive environment and encourage the individual&#8217;s participation in the treatment process.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Are there educational programs about addiction in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, many universities and institutions organize educational programs on combating addiction and work to raise awareness among young people.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-04-20T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:51:15Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'combating-addiction-and-support-services-in-turkey';
