ption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey/","name":"Medical Evacuation and Emergency Health Travel in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-20T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-20T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Medical Evacuation and Emergency Health Travel in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-04-20T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-04-20T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about medical evacuation and emergency health travel services available in Turkey. Understand the process, requirements, and insurance options for safe and rapid medical transport.","name":"Medical Evacuation and Emergency Health Travel in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<h2 id="turkiyede-tibbi-tahliye-nedir-ve-neden-onemlidir" class="wp-block-heading">What is Medical Evacuation in Turkey and Why is it Important?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Medical evacuation refers to the emergency transport of patients to another medical facility or country as required by their health condition. With its strategic geographical location and advanced healthcare infrastructure, Turkey has become a major hub for medical evacuation services. These services are of vital importance, especially in cases of natural disasters, accidents, or sudden health problems.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">The Importance of Medical Evacuation</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Need for Emergency Intervention:</strong> It is essential for patients in critical condition to be quickly transported to a better-equipped medical facility.</li>
<li><strong>Expertise and Equipment:</strong> Turkey offers high-quality healthcare services in various medical specialties, ensuring patients have access to the best possible treatment.</li>
<li><strong>International Standards:</strong> Medical institutions in Turkey provide services in accordance with international healthcare standards.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="acil-saglik-seyahati-surec-ve-gereksinimler" class="wp-block-heading">Emergency Health Travel: Process and Requirements</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Emergency health travel is a process that ensures the rapid transport of patients in urgent situations. This process is typically carried out using air ambulances or ground ambulances. The basic requirements for emergency health travel are as follows:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Patient&#8217;s Condition:</strong> The patient&#8217;s health status determines the mode of travel and the necessary medical equipment.</li>
<li><strong>Medical Team:</strong> A medical team must be assigned to accompany the patient during travel.</li>
<li><strong>Documents:</strong> Documents related to the patient&#8217;s health condition must be prepared before the journey.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">The Emergency Health Travel Process</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Condition Assessment:</strong> The patient&#8217;s health status is evaluated by the medical team.</li>
<li><strong>Transport Planning:</strong> A plan is created to transport the patient to the most suitable medical facility.</li>
<li><strong>Transportation:</strong> The patient is transported safely and securely.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-tibbi-tahliye-hizmetleri-hangi-secenekler-mevcut" class="wp-block-heading">Medical Evacuation Services in Turkey: What Options Are Available?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are various organizations in Turkey that offer medical evacuation services. These services generally include the following options:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Air Ambulances:</strong> Air ambulances that provide rapid transportation for patients in emergencies.</li>
<li><strong>Ground Ambulances:</strong> Ambulances used for transport to local hospitals or medical facilities.</li>
<li><strong>Medical Equipment:</strong> Necessary medical equipment and expert personnel during transport.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Organizations Providing Medical Evacuation Services</h3>
<p>Companies with extensive networks across Turkey include <b>Medline</b>, <b>Dolunay Ambulans</b>, <b>Has Ambulans</b>, and <b>Özel Emas Ambulans</b>.</p>
<p><b>Some Prominent Names:</b> Companies with many years of experience in this field and that conduct international operations include <b>S.O.S Air (S.O.S International)</b>, <b>Plures Air</b>, and <b>Dolunay Ambulans</b>.</p>
<p><b>Service Area:</b> First response in emergencies and hospital transfers. They also handle inter-hospital transfers for critical patients upon a physician&#8217;s decision.</p>
<p><b>Scope:</b> Intra-city and inter-city ground transportation.</p>
<p><b>Services:</b> Air ambulance rental, <b>Medical Escort</b> services on scheduled flights, and organization of all international bureaucratic permits.</p>
<p>In Turkey, <b>medical evacuation (medical transfer)</b> services are provided by both the public sector (Ministry of Health) and a wide network of private companies. The choice of organization often depends on the urgency of the patient&#8217;s condition, the distance of the transfer, and your budget.</p>
<p>Here are the main categories of organizations that offer medical evacuation services in Turkey:</p>
<h3>1. Public Institutions (Ministry of Health)</h3>
<p>These services are typically used for patients in life-threatening conditions who require an urgent transfer. Operated by the state, these systems provide services free of charge.</p>
<h4>A. 112 Emergency Services</h4>
<h4 id="tibbi-tahliye-surecinde-hangi-belgeler-gereklidir" class="wp-block-heading">What Documents are Required for the Medical Evacuation Process?</h4>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During the medical evacuation process, certain documents related to the patient&#8217;s condition must be prepared. These documents are important for ensuring the process proceeds smoothly. The required documents include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Patient&#8217;s Medical Report:</strong> A detailed report on the patient&#8217;s health condition.</li>
<li><strong>Transportation Permits:</strong> The necessary permits for medical evacuation.</li>
<li><strong>Insurance Documents:</strong> Documents showing the scope of <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-ogrenci-saglik-sigortasi-secenekleri/">health insurance</a> coverage during the travel.</li>
<li><strong>Identification Documents:</strong> Documents containing the patient&#8217;s identification information.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-acil-saglik-seyahati-sigorta-kapsami-ve-onemi" class="wp-block-heading">Emergency Health Travel in Turkey: Insurance Coverage and Importance</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For emergency health travel, insurance plays a critical role in reducing potential financial burdens for patients. Health insurance covers expenses that patients may encounter during their treatment. In Turkey, insurance coverage for emergency health travel is as follows:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Emergency Medical Treatment:</strong> Covers the costs of the patient&#8217;s treatment in emergency situations.</li>
<li><strong>Transportation Costs:</strong> Covers transportation expenses that may arise during medical evacuation.</li>
<li><strong>Hospital Costs:</strong> Covers the patient&#8217;s hospital expenses during the treatment process.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Insurance Options</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Private Health Insurance:</strong> Private insurance companies offer various policies for emergency health travel.</li>
<li><strong>State Insurance:</strong> Some state insurance plans may be valid in emergency health situations.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How do medical evacuation services work in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, medical evacuation services are planned according to the patient&#8217;s health condition and are usually carried out by air or ground ambulances.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What documents are required for emergency health travel?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For emergency health travel, the patient&#8217;s medical report, transportation permits, insurance documents, and identification documents are required.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Who provides medical evacuation services in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, medical evacuation services are provided by private medical institutions, public hospitals, and international health companies.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Does insurance cover emergency health travel?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, health insurance for emergency health travel typically covers emergency medical treatment, transportation, and hospital costs.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Who accompanies the patient during a medical evacuation?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During the medical evacuation process, the patient is usually accompanied by medical personnel, such as a doctor and a nurse.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-04-20T07:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:51:14Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'medical-evacuation-and-emergency-health-travel-in-turkey' );
