<td>Communication Channel</td>
<td>Note</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><b>For Citizens of Your Own Country</b></td>
<td><b>Embassy/Consulate On-Duty Hotline</b></td>
<td>Each mission publishes a 24/7 emergency phone number on its website. These lines usually only serve citizens of that specific country.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>For Turkish Citizens (While Abroad)</b></td>
<td><b>Republic of Turkey Ministry of Foreign Affairs Consular Call Center</b></td>
<td><b>+90 312 292 29 29</b> (operates 24/7).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>General Information for Foreigners</b></td>
<td><b>YİMER 157 (Foreigners&#8217; Communication Center)</b></td>
<td>Provides 24/7 service on topics such as visas, residence permits, international protection, and reporting migrant smuggling.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Life-Threatening Situations</b></td>
<td><b>112 (Emergency Call Center)</b></td>
<td>The single number for Police, Gendarmerie, Fire Department, Ambulance, and Forest Fire services. You can also receive service in foreign languages.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2>3. Consular Emergency Assistance Procedures</h2>
<p>When you request help from your consulate in an emergency, you can generally receive the following services:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Medical Assistance:</b> Referral to a hospital, contacting your insurance company or family. Helping you organize the process if a medical evacuation (air ambulance, etc.) is required.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Document Assistance:</b> Issuing a <b>temporary travel document</b> (Emergency Travel Document) to enable your return to your home country if your passport is lost.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Legal Support:</b> In case of arrest or detention, providing a list of lawyers and visiting you (if permitted).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Financial Assistance:</b> Helping to deliver money sent from family, friends, or your insurance company, or providing a <b>loan</b> up to the limits set by your country (only for some countries).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Family Communication:</b> Informing your family in serious situations like illness, accident, or death.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3>Important Reminder</h3>
<p>Remember that consulates:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Cannot get you out of prison or interfere with Turkish legal processes.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Will not pay your legal fees or fines.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cannot replace your lost or stolen money.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Therefore, it is vital to <b>save your emergency contact number</b> and purchase <b>comprehensive <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-seyahat-sagligi-onlemler/">travel health insurance</a></b> before traveling to Turkey.</p>
</div>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are consular services?</h3>
<p>Consular services handle and provide support for citizens&#8217; procedures abroad, such as <strong>birth, death, marriage, passport, military service, notary, and emergency</strong> (detention, accident) matters.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the number +90 312 292 29 29 for?</h3>
<p>This number belongs to the <strong>Republic of Turkey Ministry of Foreign Affairs Consular Call Center</strong> and provides 24/7 service for consular procedures for Turkish citizens abroad.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the Consular Call Center phone number?</h3>
<p>The phone number for the Republic of Turkey Ministry of Foreign Affairs Consular Call Center is <strong>+90 312 292 29 29</strong> when called from within Turkey. Different lines are available from abroad.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the consulate&#8217;s WhatsApp number?</h3>
<p>The Republic of Turkey Ministry of Foreign Affairs&#8217; Consular Call Center does not have a direct <strong>WhatsApp number</strong>. Communication is handled via phone or email.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-04-19T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:51:13Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-consular-emergency-services-in-turkey' );
